name: Julie Hedgepeth Williams
text: This is the best-kept recreation secret in Birmingham!  Inexpensive, uncrowded, refreshing.  It only costs $1 to swim from noon-6 Monday-Saturday, and it's free Monday and Thursday nights 6-7.  There's a free swim team for kids up to age 18, and if you swim on the team, you swim free any other time.  Can't swim?  There are Red Cross lessons for, I think, $5 for two weeks.  The only problem?  The city pools, including Underwood, are run by teachers, so they close when teachers go back to school.  This year (2015), teachers go back Aug. 5, so the pool closes July 31.  That's a true bummer!

text: It's an ok place to let the kids play but don't be sucked in to the fraudulently advertised swim lessons. They are simply charging you $30 per person to play in the pool with the other kids who each pay $30 to be there. The life guards are only there to flirt with one another and quote their favorite movie lines or song lyrics. With each day of lessons they would start later and end earlier than the scheduled times.     If there is a plus at all It is that my children did like playing in the pool but I would have preferred  to take them on my schedule instead of paying $60 to show up for non existent lessons.
